---
import Verticalgrid from "../assets/VerticalGrid.astro";
---
<section aria-labelledby="Faqtwo" id="Faqtwo " class="relative">
  <Verticalgrid />
  <div class="max-w-7xl px-8 md:px-12 lg:px-32 mx-auto py-12 lg:pt-24 relative">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center">
      <div>
        <span
          class="text-transparent bg-clip-text font-medium tracking-widest bg-gradient-to-r from-cyan-400 via-teal-500 to-indigo-500 text-xs uppercase"
          >Faq 2</span
        ><p class="text-3xl mt-8 font-normal text-white">
          Fully automated, fully supported
        </p>
        <p class="max-w-xl mx-auto mt-4 text-lg text-slate-400">
          Self-serve or work with a representative, we're here to help with the
          capital journey that works for you.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="max-w-7xl px-8 md:px-12 lg:px-32 mx-auto py-12 lg:py-24 relative">
    <div
      class="relative mx-auto border rounded-3xl border-white/5 bg-vulcan-900"
      x-data="{selected:null}">
      <ul class="list-none" role="list" @click="open = !open">
        <li class="relative border-b border-white/5">
          <button
            type="button"
            class="w-full px-8 py-6 text-left"
            @click="selected !== 1 ? selected = 1 : selected = null">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between text-white">
              <p
                class="text-sm text-slate-400 hover:text-cyan-400 duration-200">
                Can I use Unwrapped for client projects?
              </p>
              <svg
                :class="{'rotate-180': open, 'rotate-0': !open}"
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                class="inline w-5 h-5 ml-4 transition-transform duration-200 transform rotate-180"
                viewBox="0 0 20 20"
                fill="currentColor">
                <path
                  fill-rule="evenodd"
                  d="M14.707 12.707a1 1 0 01-1.414 0L10 9.414l-3.293 3.293a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414l4-4a1 1 0 011.414 0l4 4a1 1 0 010 1.414z"
                  clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
          <div
            class="relative overflow-hidden transition-all duration-700 max-h-0"
            style=""
            x-ref="container1"
            x-bind:style="selected == 1 ? 'max-height: ' + $refs.container1.scrollHeight + 'px' : ''">
            <div class="px-8 pt-4 pb-20 text-slate-400 text-sm">
              Aye! You can do so, what you are not allowed is using it to create
              derivative competing products.
            </div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="relative border-b border-white/5">
          <button
            type="button"
            class="w-full px-8 py-6 text-left"
            @click="selected !== 2 ? selected = 2 : selected = null">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between text-white">
              <p
                class="text-sm text-slate-400 hover:text-cyan-400 duration-200">
                Where is Unwrapped made?
              </p>
              <svg
                :class="{'rotate-180': open, 'rotate-0': !open}"
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                class="inline w-5 h-5 ml-4 transition-transform duration-200 transform rotate-180"
                viewBox="0 0 20 20"
                fill="currentColor">
                <path
                  fill-rule="evenodd"
                  d="M14.707 12.707a1 1 0 01-1.414 0L10 9.414l-3.293 3.293a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414l4-4a1 1 0 011.414 0l4 4a1 1 0 010 1.414z"
                  clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
          <div
            class="relative overflow-hidden transition-all duration-700 max-h-0"
            style=""
            x-ref="container2"
            x-bind:style="selected == 2 ? 'max-height: ' + $refs.container2.scrollHeight + 'px' : ''">
            <div class="px-8 pt-4 pb-20 text-slate-400 text-sm">
              The wireframes are built for Figma
            </div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="relative border-b border-white/5">
          <button
            type="button"
            class="w-full px-8 py-6 text-left"
            @click="selected !== 3 ? selected = 3 : selected = null">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between text-white">
              <p
                class="text-sm text-slate-400 hover:text-cyan-400 duration-200">
                Can I use Unwrapped for open source projects?
              </p>
              <svg
                :class="{'rotate-180': open, 'rotate-0': !open}"
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                class="inline w-5 h-5 ml-4 transition-transform duration-200 transform rotate-180"
                viewBox="0 0 20 20"
                fill="currentColor">
                <path
                  fill-rule="evenodd"
                  d="M14.707 12.707a1 1 0 01-1.414 0L10 9.414l-3.293 3.293a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414l4-4a1 1 0 011.414 0l4 4a1 1 0 010 1.414z"
                  clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
          <div
            class="relative overflow-hidden transition-all duration-700 max-h-0"
            style=""
            x-ref="container2"
            x-bind:style="selected == 3 ? 'max-height: ' + $refs.container2.scrollHeight + 'px' : ''">
            <div class="px-8 pt-4 pb-20 text-slate-400 text-sm">
              Of course, but only if this is a website and not a derivative
              component library, theme builder, or other product where the
              primary purpose is clearly to bundle and/or redistribute
              Unwrapped.
            </div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="relative border-b border-white/5">
          <button
            type="button"
            class="w-full px-8 py-6 text-left"
            @click="selected !== 4 ? selected = 4 : selected = null">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between text-white">
              <p
                class="text-sm text-slate-400 hover:text-cyan-400 duration-200">
                Can I sell templates/themes that I made with Unwrapped?
              </p>
              <svg
                :class="{'rotate-180': open, 'rotate-0': !open}"
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                class="inline w-5 h-5 ml-4 transition-transform duration-200 transform rotate-180"
                viewBox="0 0 20 20"
                fill="currentColor">
                <path
                  fill-rule="evenodd"
                  d="M14.707 12.707a1 1 0 01-1.414 0L10 9.414l-3.293 3.293a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414l4-4a1 1 0 011.414 0l4 4a1 1 0 010 1.414z"
                  clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
          <div
            class="relative overflow-hidden transition-all duration-700 max-h-0"
            style=""
            x-ref="container2"
            x-bind:style="selected == 4 ? 'max-height: ' + $refs.container2.scrollHeight + 'px' : ''">
            <div class="px-8 pt-4 pb-20 text-slate-400 text-sm">
              Absolutely not. You can't to create derivative products like
              themes, UI kits, page builders, or anything else where you
              supplying the resources for someone else to use to build their own
              website.
            </div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="relative border-b border-white/5">
          <button
            type="button"
            class="w-full px-8 py-6 text-left"
            @click="selected !== 5 ? selected = 5 : selected = null">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between text-white">
              <p
                class="text-sm text-slate-400 hover:text-cyan-400 duration-200">
                Can I use Unwrapped for the commercial projects that I work on?
              </p>
              <svg
                :class="{'rotate-180': open, 'rotate-0': !open}"
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                class="inline w-5 h-5 ml-4 transition-transform duration-200 transform rotate-180"
                viewBox="0 0 20 20"
                fill="currentColor">
                <path
                  fill-rule="evenodd"
                  d="M14.707 12.707a1 1 0 01-1.414 0L10 9.414l-3.293 3.293a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414l4-4a1 1 0 011.414 0l4 4a1 1 0 010 1.414z"
                  clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
          <div
            class="relative overflow-hidden transition-all duration-700 max-h-0"
            style=""
            x-ref="container2"
            x-bind:style="selected == 5 ? 'max-height: ' + $refs.container2.scrollHeight + 'px' : ''">
            <div class="px-8 pt-4 pb-20 text-slate-400 text-sm">
              Sure you can. The license allows you to build as many of your own
              projects as you want and need, no matter if this are public
              websites or SaaS applications.
            </div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="relative border-b border-white/5">
          <button
            type="button"
            class="w-full px-8 py-6 text-left"
            @click="selected !== 6 ? selected = 6 : selected = null">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between text-white">
              <p
                class="text-sm text-slate-400 hover:text-cyan-400 duration-200">
                What does "free updates" include?
              </p>
              <svg
                :class="{'rotate-180': open, 'rotate-0': !open}"
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                class="inline w-5 h-5 ml-4 transition-transform duration-200 transform rotate-180"
                viewBox="0 0 20 20"
                fill="currentColor">
                <path
                  fill-rule="evenodd"
                  d="M14.707 12.707a1 1 0 01-1.414 0L10 9.414l-3.293 3.293a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414l4-4a1 1 0 011.414 0l4 4a1 1 0 010 1.414z"
                  clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
          <div
            class="relative overflow-hidden transition-all duration-700 max-h-0"
            style=""
            x-ref="container2"
            x-bind:style="selected == 6 ? 'max-height: ' + $refs.container2.scrollHeight + 'px' : ''">
            <div class="px-8 pt-4 pb-20 text-slate-400 text-sm">
              I keep adding new wireframes so all of them become free for
              existing customers.
            </div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <!----- Last -->
        <li class="relative">
          <button
            type="button"
            class="w-full px-8 py-6 text-left"
            @click="selected !== 7 ? selected = 7 : selected = null">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between text-white">
              <p
                class="text-sm text-slate-400 hover:text-cyan-400 duration-200">
                What does your refund policy?
              </p>
              <svg
                :class="{'rotate-180': open, 'rotate-0': !open}"
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                class="inline w-5 h-5 ml-4 transition-transform duration-200 transform rotate-180"
                viewBox="0 0 20 20"
                fill="currentColor">
                <path
                  fill-rule="evenodd"
                  d="M14.707 12.707a1 1 0 01-1.414 0L10 9.414l-3.293 3.293a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414l4-4a1 1 0 011.414 0l4 4a1 1 0 010 1.414z"
                  clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
          <div
            class="relative overflow-hidden transition-all duration-700 max-h-0"
            style=""
            x-ref="container3"
            x-bind:style="selected == 7 ? 'max-height: ' + $refs.container3.scrollHeight + 'px' : ''">
            <div class="px-8 pt-4 pb-20 text-slate-400 text-sm">
              If you’re not satisfied, please contact me and describe the refund
              reason. Once I receive your refund request, I will inspect it and
              notify you about the decision. Usually, I can’t make a refund
              because the product is digital. But I am responsible for the
              quality of the products and provide a refund if you’re not
              satisfied with it. The return right applies to all products
              presented on the unwrapped.design website.
            </div>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
